    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-11T06:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-11T06:25:00-05:00" n="605"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d605">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/555: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">George</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-11T14:00:00+02:35"
                            >July 11, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 11—12:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>58. Department’s telegram 31, July 5, 5 p.m. Emperor’s reaction to American reply
                    very satisfactory. He has stated that reply is “better than expected”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
